3E%3Cspan%3EHaving%20a%20graduate%20degree%20in%20psychology%2C%20I%20understood%20this%20was%20a%20normal%2C%20healthy%20part%20of%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpep-web.org%2Fbrowse%2Fdocument%2FPSC.022.0162A%3Fpage%3DP0162%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20adolescent%20individuation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20process%20that%20allows%20teens%20to%20fully%20develop%20their%20sense%20of%20self%20and%20become%20functioning%20adults.%20But%20nothing%20prepared%20me%20for%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmolly-shannons-advice-parents-raising-teens-see-them-regular-people-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emessiness%20of%20my%20own%20emotions%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20I%20was%20horrified%20to%20find%20myself%20peppering%20her%20with%20questions%2C%20barging%20in%20on%20her%20conversations%2C%20and%20feeling%20hurt%20when%20her%20dad%20knew%20something%20I%20didn't.%20My%20sadness%20had%20me%20holding%20on%20tighter%20when%20I%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20letting%20go.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThe%20feeling%20of%20grief%20is%20sometimes%20surprising%20to%20people%20because%20they%20don't%20see%20it%20as%20grief%2C%26quot%3B%20explained%20my%20neighbor%20Carla%20Corral%2C%20a%20licensed%20clinical%20psychologist%20whose%20oldest%20daughter%20is%20a%20sophomore%20in%20college.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20losing%20somebody%2C%20right%2C%20to%20death%20or%20illness%20or%20the%20abrupt%20end%20of%20a%20relationship%2C%20but%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-and-counselor-on-what-parents-should-know-about-grief-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eit's%20grief%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20didn't%20like%20the%20way%20my%20grief%20had%20me%20inserting%20myself%20into%20my%20daughter's%20life.%20I%20felt%20needy%2C%20clingy%2C%20and%20decidedly%20not%20cool.%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20push%20her%20away%20or%20make%20her%20feel%20she%20needed%20to%20care%20for%20my%20feelings.%20It%20was%20time%20to%20get%20hold%20of%20myself.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22911b9894-7c69-4285-a8a6-aecc94d99beb%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20had%20to%20change%20my%20behavior%20or%20risk%20pushing%20her%20away%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20thought%20back%20to%20how%20exciting%20life%20was%20when%20I%20was%20her%20age%20and%20how%20eager%20and%20capable%20I%20felt.%20Shifting%20away%20from%20my%20current%20point%20of%20view%20as%20a%20concerned%20mom%20helped%20me%20see%20how%20smart%2C%20responsible%2C%20and%20prepared%20my%20daughter%20is.%20I%20also%20turned%20my%20attention%20back%20on%20myself%20and%20my%20dreams%20for%20the%20future.%20I%20grew%20up%20dancing%2C%20so%20I%20joined%20a%20tap%20class.%20It's%20great%20exercise%20and%20so%20much%20fun.%20Instead%20of%20gifts%20for%20Christmas%2C%20I%20gave%20my%20friends%20a%20breakfast%20or%20lunch%20date%20to%20prioritize%20connecting%20one-on-one.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20started%20journaling%20again%20to%20dump%20my%20worries%20on%20the%20page%20instead%20of%20on%20my%20daughter.%20This%20helped%20me%20see%20some%20of%20my%20concerns%20as%20ridiculous%20and%20others%20as%20important%20points%20to%20discuss%20before%20she%20leaves.%20I%20keep%20reminding%20myself%20my%20job%20as%20a%20parent%20is%20shifting%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20over.%20Making%20my%20life%20more%20about%20me%20again%20allowed%20those%20clingy%20behaviors%20to%20fade%20away%2C%20and%20when%20they%20occasionally%20pop%20up%2C%20I%20take%20a%20deep%20breath%20and%20focus%20on%20something%20I%20enjoy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20I%20soak%20up%20the%20time%20I%20have%20with%20her%20%E2%80%94%20including%20family%20movie%20nights%2C%20a%20spring%20break%20trip%20to%20visit%20her%20top%20choi